{"id":8292,"date":"2024-01-23T12:50:50","date_gmt":"2020-04-23T07:20:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=8292"},"modified":"2024-10-26T12:42:02","modified_gmt":"2024-10-26T07:12:02","slug":"minimalistic-living-room","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/minimalistic-living-room\/","title":{"rendered":"Minimalistic Living Room Design Ideas For Your Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>It is impossible to negate the tranquillity and simple beauty of a resolved minimalist interior. But, ask any interior designer and they will tell you that achieving a minimalistic look can be challenging. You don\u2019t want your room to look cluttered but at the same time if minimalism goes wrong it can leave the space feeling cold and unlived-in. To help you in your minimalistic journey, Design Caf\u00e9 brings you living room design ideas where a smart selection of \u2018less is more\u2019.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Attention To Scale Is Important<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalistic living rooms and small spaces get along beautifully. You can make a few design changes to make the most of available space without making your space look cluttered. For example, ditch the traditional five to seven seater sofa set and settle for a small L-shaped sofa instead. Add some ottoman or comfy chair to increase seating space as well as to add variety to the living room. Replace the bulky coffee table with something chic yet compact as seen in the picture below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/22204342\/minimalist-living-room.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist living room where attention to scale in important with small L-shaped sofa \" class=\"wp-image-8294\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/22204342\/minimalist-living-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/22204342\/minimalist-living-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/22204342\/minimalist-living-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/22204342\/minimalist-living-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Muted Colours to Break The Monochrome<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p> If you are rooting for minimalist design but do not want to stay away from colours, this living room in the image here is your guide to follow. The sofa set, curtains and other finishes follow a monochrome scheme giving this space a unified and clean look. And then, they introduce dynamism through a contrasting wallpaper and a muted carpet. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23183446\/minimalist-living-room-small-space-with-muted-colours.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist living room small space with  sofa set, curtains and other finishes follow a monochrome scheme \" class=\"wp-image-8351\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23183446\/minimalist-living-room-small-space-with-muted-colours.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23183446\/minimalist-living-room-small-space-with-muted-colours-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23183446\/minimalist-living-room-small-space-with-muted-colours-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23183446\/minimalist-living-room-small-space-with-muted-colours-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The contrasting artwork speaks volume and is not loud<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Go All White For A Cozy Minimalist Living Room<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p> Why use colour when you can create an incredible minimalistic d\u00e9cor by going all white? This will make the process a lot easier as it gives a space a complete look because all elements in this palette by default go together. And going all-white doesn\u2019t mean that the fun quotient should be missing. It is about playing with shapes, textures, and elements. For example, in this minimalistic style living room below, the designer has placed a statement lamp along with a few greens for a more natural, earthy look. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23184157\/cozy-minimalist-living-room-with-all-white-colour.jpg\" alt=\"Cozy minimalist living room with all white colour with different shapes, textures, and elements\" class=\"wp-image-8353\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23184157\/cozy-minimalist-living-room-with-all-white-colour.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23184157\/cozy-minimalist-living-room-with-all-white-colour-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23184157\/cozy-minimalist-living-room-with-all-white-colour-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23184157\/cozy-minimalist-living-room-with-all-white-colour-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Beautifully blended in an all-white colour scheme<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Feature One Statement Piece<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In this minimalistic interior, the designer has opted for an all-white sofa. He even opted out of cushions or comfy pillows. But to pop the colour, the designer just placed one item in a really bright colour \u2013 a dark blue chair. It becomes the centre of attraction and manages to have your attention as long as you are in the room. For a more minimalistic look, you can do without the striped wallpaper and opt for an all-white look instead <\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23185953\/minimalist-living-room-apartment-with-all-white-sofa-1.jpg\" alt=\"minimalist living room apartment with a white sofa and a dark blue chair\" class=\"wp-image-8355\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23185953\/minimalist-living-room-apartment-with-all-white-sofa-1.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23185953\/minimalist-living-room-apartment-with-all-white-sofa-1-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23185953\/minimalist-living-room-apartment-with-all-white-sofa-1-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23185953\/minimalist-living-room-apartment-with-all-white-sofa-1-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A vibrant accent piece livens up this living room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"941\" height=\"2743\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations.jpg\" alt=\"Six trendy colour combinations for a stylish living room design\" class=\"wp-image-60110\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations.jpg 941w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations-103x300.jpg 103w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations-351x1024.jpg 351w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations-768x2239.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations-527x1536.jpg 527w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations-703x2048.jpg 703w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/26124133\/6-living-room-colour-combinations-150x437.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 941px) 100vw, 941px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Say Hello To Monochromes<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Monochrome is the king when it comes to minimalist design. The living room set-up below is a perfect example of \u2018less is more\u2019. A clean and well-organised combination of sofa set, monochrome pillows, and a carpet to keep things interesting and serene. Then add a glass coffee table for an easy and stylish <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/small-living-room-decorating-ideas\/\">living room d\u00e9cor<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190319\/minimalist-living-room-india-with-monochrome.jpg\" alt=\"minimalist living room india with sofa set, monochrome pillows and a glass coffee table \" class=\"wp-image-8356\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190319\/minimalist-living-room-india-with-monochrome.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190319\/minimalist-living-room-india-with-monochrome-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190319\/minimalist-living-room-india-with-monochrome-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190319\/minimalist-living-room-india-with-monochrome-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\"> The carpet beautifully holds everything together in this monochrome scheme<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Incorporate Wood Inspired Minimalistic Designs<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Who said you cannot use wood or wood-inspired designs in a cozy minimalist living room? The room by Design Caf\u00e9 is a breath of fresh air among monochromatic looks. The cozy coffee table is a perfect example of fun yet formal <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">interior design<\/a>. The matching side seating arrangement, TV cabinet, chair, and natural rug make for an eclectic combination of earthy and natural tones.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190635\/minimalist-living-room-without-sofa-with-wood-inspired.jpg\" alt=\"minimalist living room without sofa with wood inspired designs and a cozy coffee table, tv cabinet and chair\" class=\"wp-image-8358\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190635\/minimalist-living-room-without-sofa-with-wood-inspired.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190635\/minimalist-living-room-without-sofa-with-wood-inspired-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190635\/minimalist-living-room-without-sofa-with-wood-inspired-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190635\/minimalist-living-room-without-sofa-with-wood-inspired-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The woody tones set the mood for a relaxed and sophisticated living area<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Go For An Amalgamation of Colours<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In this timeless room in the image below, the minimal theme gets a twist with an amalgamation of bright colours and earthy hues. The classic grey chair and simple coffee table go well with the minimalistic theme. And the colourful lamp shades add much needed drama.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190936\/small-apartment-living-room-ideas-minimalist.jpg\" alt=\"small apartment living room ideas minimalist with bright colours, classic grey chair and simple coffee table \" class=\"wp-image-8359\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190936\/small-apartment-living-room-ideas-minimalist.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190936\/small-apartment-living-room-ideas-minimalist-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190936\/small-apartment-living-room-ideas-minimalist-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/04\/23190936\/small-apartment-living-room-ideas-minimalist-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">The combination of blue, yellow and earthy tones is a treat for the eyes\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Minimalist architecture for the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/interior-design\/living-room-design\/\">living room interior<\/a> demands the use of nominal design elements, without going over the top with ornamentation or decoration. It allows things other than the space to be in focus. And most importantly, every item in a minimalistic style living room needs to be functional and add value to the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>What do you think? Let us know in the comments section.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, check out <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/living-room-interiors\/colour-combination-for-living-room\/\">8 Best Colour Combinations For Your Living Room<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Dreamy Interiors That Spell 'WOW'<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Speak to our design experts today!<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n                    selected>\n                    +91\n                <\/option